SUMMARY:135th SF Hardware Meetup @ Antler VC | Demo Night
LOCATION:San Francisco\, California
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin us for our 135th SF Hardware Meetup as a s
 ummer happy hour.\n\n🤖 Bring physical demos! It can be products\, proto
 types\, components\, or anything physical. We're doing this happy hour sty
 le with walk around demos.\n\nComment in this doc to sign up for a demo sp
 ot.\n\n​Shout-out to our venue partner!\n\nAntler: The world’s leading
  inception-stage investor\, backing founders at day zero and supporting th
 em as they build era-defining companies. On a monthly basis\, Antler bring
 s together a curated group of operators\, builders\, and founders to work 
 side-by-side for up to three months before pitching their investment commi
 ttee for an initial $500K–$1M commitment.\n\nAgenda\n\nThere is no set a
 genda. This is a casual happy hour with walk around demos and mix + mingle
  style experience.\n\n​​​Thank you to our community partners!\n\ninf
 ormal is a freelance collective for the most talented independent professi
 onals in hardware. Whether you're looking for a single contractor\, a full
 -time employee\, or an entire team of professionals to work on everything 
 from product development to go-to-market\, the informal collective has the
  perfect collection of people for the job. Learn more.\n\nIf you want to h
 elp support the next meetup\, please reach out to michael (at) hardwaremee
 tup (dot) com for sponsorship inquiries.\n​​See you soon!\n\nThis even
 t is part of SF Hardware Meetup\, which hosts monthly demo nights. Hardwar
 e Meetup meets across 40+ cities with 40k members.\n\nHardware Meetup is a
  volunteer organization and relies on sponsorships to cover the costs of p
 utting on these events.\n\nWe share the RSVP list with sponsors who suppor
 t 3 or more events. By RSVPing to this event you consent to us sharing you
 r email address and other registration information with our sponsors.\n\nB
 y registering for this event\, you agree to share your registration inform
 ation with the organizers of SF Climate Week.\n\nCalendar: SF Hardware Mee
 tup\n\nHosts: Michael Raspuzzi\, Nate Padgett\, Garvin Meyers\, Miguel A V
 illafuerte\, Mariana Ortiz\, Tyler Lux\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/bo5
 8tyyg
URL:https://luma.com/bo58tyyg
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
