SUMMARY:GTLC Bay Area Chinese Tech Leaders Summit
LOCATION:Q Bay Center\, San Jose\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nOrganized by TGO 鲲鹏会\, the GTLC Bay Area 
 Chinese Tech Leaders Summit is a full-day summit for Chinese technology le
 aders across the Bay Area and North America.\n\nThe 2026 summit theme is T
 he Age of Autonomous Systems. As AI moves from copilots and chatbots towar
 d agents\, autonomous workflows\, self-improving systems\, robotics\, and 
 AI-native organizations\, technology leaders are facing a new set of quest
 ions: how to build these systems\, how to organize teams around them\, and
  where the next wave of startup and industry opportunities will emerge.\n\
 nConfirmed keynote speakers\nJuly 17\, 2026\, full day\n\nYuandong Tian (
 田渊栋)\, Co-founder of Recursive Superintelligence\n\nYangqing Jia（
 贾扬清）\, VP of NVIDIA\; Co-founder & CEO of Lepton AI\n\nDongxu Huan
 g（黄东旭）\, Summit Co-Chair\; Co-founder & CTO of TiDB\n\nJunchen J
 iang（江鋆晨）\, CEO & Co-founder of Tensormesh\; Professor at UChica
 go\n\nYi Zhu\, Founder of Humani Labs\; Co-founder of Boson AI\n\nJunwei Z
 hang（张俊伟）\, Host of The Diff Podcast\; Board Member of TGO Silic
 on Valley\n\nThe summit will also feature many other industry leaders\, fo
 unders\, senior engineers\, and technology executives from the Chinese tec
 h community in the Bay Area and beyond.\n\nTarget audience\n\nTech leads\,
  engineering managers\, AI professionals\, entrepreneurs\, investors\, sta
 rtup founders\, and members of the broader Chinese technology community in
  North America.\n\nKey themes\n\nAutonomous systems and AI agents\n\nAI te
 chnology trends\n\nTechnology leadership\n\nEngineering organization and m
 anagement\n\nStartup practices in the AI era\n\nEmerging technology and in
 vestment opportunities\n\nCross-border perspectives from Chinese tech lead
 ers\n\nOverview\n\nThe summit brings together around 300 Chinese technolog
 y and entrepreneurial professionals from the Bay Area and North America fo
 r a day of talks\, discussions\, and high-quality offline networking.\n\nT
 he program includes keynote speeches\, lightning talks\, panel discussions
 \, lunch networking\, and interactive sessions. The main stage will focus 
 on the summit theme\, The Age of Autonomous Systems\, while breakout sessi
 ons will go deeper into:\n\nAI technology trends\n\nOrganization and leade
 rship in the AI era\n\nVoices from China\, featuring sharing sessions from
  TGO China members\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: TGO-US\, Yue Guo\n\nVen
 ue: Q Bay Center\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/oym92m2s
URL:https://luma.com/oym92m2s
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
