DTEND:20260719T040000Z
SUMMARY:AI Valley x Pet Zen Dog-a-thon
LOCATION:San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nDogathon — AI Valley × PetZen 🐶\n\nA hack
 athon where every project has a real dog on the other end of it.\n\n200 de
 velopers\, designers\, AI builders\, vet techs\, and shelter volunteers ar
 e coming together to build tools that directly support rescue operations a
 nd dog adoption.\n\nThe day begins with rescue dogs meeting participants o
 n-site. Teams will then spend the rest of the hackathon building products 
 that help shelters\, rescues\, fosters\, adopters\, and dogs themselves 
 — from adoption matching tools and volunteer coordination systems to AI 
 copilots for rescue operations.\n\nOur rescue partner will be present thro
 ughout the event\, so anyone who forms a connection with a dog during the 
 morning meet-and-greet can begin the adoption process on-site.\n\nNot anot
 her demo-day hackathon.\nBuild something that actually helps a living bein
 g.\n\n🐾 What to expect:\n\nReal rescue dogs on-site\n\nBuilders\, desig
 ners\, and animal advocates\n\nAI + software projects for rescue operation
 s\n\nMentors from tech + pet care\n\nDemos\, prizes\, and adoption opportu
 nities\n\nA high-signal\, mission-driven community\n\nMeet the dogs in the
  morning.\nBuild for them in the afternoon.\n\nRescue Partner\n\nWe’re p
 artnering with Copper’s Dream to bring adoptable dogs on-site and connec
 t builders directly with real rescue and adoption needs.\n\nSchedule\n\n9:
 00 AM — Doors open + check-in at The House by Edge & Node\n\n9:30 AM —
  Opening remarks\, challenge briefing\, and $10K+ prize pool overview\n\n1
 0:00 AM — Outdoor dog adoption and vendor area opens on Presidio Lawn #3
 \n\n10:30 AM — Problem discovery with rescue partners and team formation
 \n\n11:00 AM — Build kickoff for rescue\, adoption\, foster\, and animal
  welfare tools\n\n12:30 PM — Lunch indoors and open building continues\n
 \n1:30 PM — Mentor office hours\, sponsor support\, and product feedback
 \n\n3:00 PM — Outdoor lawn portion closes and vendor/rescue breakdown be
 gins\n\n4:30 PM — Project submission deadline\n\n5:00 PM — Final demos
  from selected teams\n\n6:00 PM — Awards\, $10K+ in prizes\, and rescue 
 impact moment\n\n6:30 PM — Community hangout and networking\n\n9:00 PM 
 — Event ends\n\nAI Valley is a community for exceptional first-generatio
 n builders\, founders\, and creators. We curate high-signal hackathons\, w
 orkshops\, and gatherings where ambitious people find collaborators\, ment
 ors\, and real opportunities. If you care about who you build with as much
  as what you build\, this is your place.\n\n🌐 Website: https://aivalley
 .io\n\n📅 Events: https://lu.ma/aivalley\n\n👥 Community (Discord): ht
 tps://discord.gg/QESCnSUPC9\n\n📰 Newsletter: https://aivalleyio.substac
 k.com\n\n🔗 All links: https://aivalley.io/links\n\nCalendar: AI Valley\
 n\nHosts: Courtney Ko\, AI Valley\, RJ\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/rkl
 rsomo
URL:https://luma.com/rklrsomo
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
